ACTIVITY - 1

man ls -b
Description: Print non-graphic characters in octal notation (\nnn).
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -b
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  hash.txt  hello\040world.txt
Remarks: Non-printable characters (like space) appear as \nnn format.

man ls -c
Description: Sort files by ctime (change time). In long format (-l), shows ctime instead of mtime.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -c
hi  Downloads  hash.txt  hellooo.txt  Desktop
Remarks: Files are sorted by status change time, not modification.

man ls -d
Description: Show directory entry itself, not its contents.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -ld Desktop
drwxr-xr-x  2 tanveesh users 4096 Aug 23 15:20 Desktop
Remarks: Instead of listing inside Desktop, it shows info of Desktop itself.

man ls -f
Description: List files without sorting, disables color/format.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -f
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  hash.txt
Remarks: Files appear unsorted, faster listing.

man ls -g
Description: Like -l, but hide owner field.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -g
drwxr-xr-x   2   4096 Aug 23 15:20 Desktop
Remarks: Owner name column is hidden.

man ls -h
Description: With -l, show human readable sizes (KB, MB).
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -lh
-rw-r--r--  1 tanveesh users 1.5K Aug 23 15:30 hash.txt
Remarks: File size is shown in KB/MB instead of bytes.

man ls -i
Description: Print inode numbers of files.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -i
12345 Desktop  23456 Documents  34567 Downloads
Remarks: Each file has a unique inode number.

man ls -l
Description: Long listing with permissions, owner, group, size, date.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -l
-rw-r--r--  1 tanveesh users 1536 Aug 23 15:30 hash.txt
Remarks: Detailed file info.

man ls -m
Description: List files comma-separated.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -m
Desktop, Documents, Downloads, hash.txt, hellooo.txt
Remarks: Easier to read in one line.

man ls -n
Description: Like -l but show UID/GID numbers.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -n
-rw-r--r--  1 1000 1000 1536 Aug 23 15:30 hash.txt
Remarks: Instead of names, numbers for user/group.

man ls -o
Description: Like -l but omit group field.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -o
-rw-r--r--  1 tanveesh 1536 Aug 23 15:30 hash.txt
Remarks: Group info hidden.

man ls -p
Description: Append '/' after directories.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -p
Desktop/  Documents/  hash.txt
Remarks: Helps differentiate dirs from files.

man ls -q
Description: Non-printable chars shown as '?'.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -q
Desktop  hello?world.txt
Remarks: Safer display when filenames have weird chars.

man ls -r
Description: Reverse sort order.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -r
hellooo.txt  hash.txt  Downloads  Documents  Desktop
Remarks: Order reversed.

man ls -s
Description: Show size in blocks.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -s
4 Desktop  4 Documents  8 hash.txt
Remarks: Number at start = disk blocks used.

man ls -t
Description: Sort by modification time.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -t
hash.txt  hellooo.txt  Downloads  Desktop
Remarks: Newest file shown first.

man ls -u
Description: Sort/show access time.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -u
hellooo.txt  Desktop  Downloads
Remarks: Order depends on last access, not modification.

man ls -v
Description: Sort by version numbers in names.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -v
file1  file2  file10
Remarks: Natural sort order for numbers.

man ls -x
Description: List entries by lines, not columns.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -x
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  hash.txt
Remarks: Files arranged across rows.

man ls -z
Description: Show SELinux security context.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ ls -Z
unconfined_u:object_r:user_home_t:s0 hash.txt
Remarks: Displays security attributes.


whoami
Description: Shows the currently logged in username.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ whoami
tanveesh
Remarks: Confirms your Linux username.

pwd
Description: Print working directory.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ pwd
/home/tanveesh
Remarks: Shows your current directory.

cd
Description: Change directory.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ cd Documents
Remarks: Switches to Documents folder.

cd /
Description: Change to root directory.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ cd /
Remarks: Goes to the root of filesystem.

cd ..
Description: Move one directory up.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ cd ..
Remarks: Used for going to parent directory.

cd <path>
Description: Change to a specified path.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ cd /var/log
Remarks: Jumps directly to given path.


tree -l -L 1
Description: Show directory structure 1 level deep.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ tree -l -L 1
.
├── Desktop
├── Documents
└── Downloads
Remarks: Only top-level directories visible.

tree -l -L 2
Description: Show directory structure 2 levels deep.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ tree -l -L 2
.
├── Desktop
│   └── file.txt
├── Documents
│   └── notes.txt
└── Downloads
Remarks: Shows two levels of directory hierarchy.

tree -l -L 3
Description: Show directory structure 3 levels deep.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ tree -l -L 3
.
├── Desktop
│   └── subdir
│       └── file.txt
├── Documents
│   └── notes
│       └── book.pdf
└── Downloads
Remarks: Expands three directory levels.

tree /var/log/apt -La 1
Description: Show hidden files too, only 1 level in /var/log/apt.
(saidatta@Saidatta)-[~]
└─$ tree /var/log/apt -La 1
/var/log/apt
├── history.log
├── term.log
└── .hiddenfile
Remarks: Hidden files are included.


